commit.message: Bump to 0.11 because of API change.

Remove HsYAML dependency.

Remove ToYAML, FromYAML instances for TemplateTarget.

[API change]

Motivation: these were needed when we used HsYAML in pandoc.
Now that we don't, they are pulling in an HsYAML dependency
we wouldn't otherwise have in pandoc.

I checked all the packages on Hackage that use doctemplates,
and none also depend on HsYAML, so I believe this won't be disruptive.
CI: test on recent GHC versions, use ghcup.
Bump to 0.10.0.2, update changelog, use doclayout 0.4.
CI: Use supported action to setup haskell.

Don't rely on aeson Object being implemented as a HashMap.

This becomes a hidden internal implementation detail in
aeson 2.0.

Change rendering and conditional behavior with booleans.

Previously, `$if(foo)$` evaluated to false iff `foo`
would render as the empty string. This forced us to render
a boolean False value as an empty string, rather than `false`.
And this has caused various problems with templates
(#16, jgm/pandoc#7402).

This commit changes two things:

- Now, boolean False values render as `false` -- just as
  True values render as `true`.
- Conditionals are now sensitive to booleans, so
  `$if(foo)$` evaluates to false when `foo` is a boolean
  False value, even though it would render as the nonempty
  string `false`.

The README on conditionals has been updated accordingly.
Hopefully solve the overlapping instance problem. (#9)

commit.message:
Add BoolVal constructor to Val.

This gives a smoother interface with JSON and YAML.
[API change]

Properly handle nested loops.

Previously "it" was always used for the variable in a loop,
and in a nested loop there was no way to distinguish the
value of the inner iteration from the value of the outer one.

Now we assign the iterated value to both "it" and to the
original variable name (e.g. "foo.bar").

This probably has a small negative performance impact.

Closes #15.
